Intesa May Expand to Turkey, Poland, Boccolini Tells Il Sole

-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 
2011-08-21T10:26:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/intesa-may-expand-to-turkey-poland-boccolini-tells-il-sole.html
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP) ,  Italy ’s second-
biggest bank, is considering expanding into Turkey and  Poland ,
Giovanni Boccolini, head of the lender’s international
subsidiary banks division, told  Il Sole 24 Ore  in an interview.  Intesa also aims to strengthen its presence in the 13
countries under his division, Boccolini told the newspaper. The
bank is satisfied with its investment in  China  where it doesn’t
currently plan to expand further, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francesca Cinelli in Milan at 
 fcinelli@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Ludden at 
 jludden@bloomberg.net  